4 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
5 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1-9-102a of Title 10A, unless
6 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
7 A. The Oklahoma Commission on Children and Youth shall provide
8 for the creation and maintenance of a secure database to be utilized
9 by freestanding multidisciplinary child abuse teams during case
10 review.
11 B. The database shall collect case information and shall
12 maintain strict security of all information. The database and its
13 use shall be subject to the confidential records requirements
14 established pursuant to Sections 1-6-102 and 1-6-107 of this title
15 and penalties for violations established pursuant to Section 1-6-107
16 of this title.
17 C. The purpose of the database shall include, but not be
18 limited to:
19 1. Facilitating case management;
20 2. Providing for appropriate and uniform collection and
21 reporting of case information by all freestanding multidisciplinary
22 child abuse teams;
23 3. Enabling Commission staff to conduct programmatic
24 evaluations; and
